    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03258.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">88 Lyon St. Ottawa</name>
                    <date when="1883-04-30">30 April 1883</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Sir,</salute>
            </opener>


            <p>I have just finished 
                reading, with intense pleasure, 
                your "Leaves of Grass." Would you forgive my 
                suggesting, as a sufficient 
                reply to your adverse critics, the
 
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03258.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.03258.004.jpg" type="verso"/> 
                
                the insertion of the
                following motto in  
                your future editions. 
                It is from the "Heauton Timorumenos" Act 1. <choice><abbr>Sc.</abbr><expan>Scene</expan></choice> 1. line 28.
                "Homo sum: humani nil a me alienum puto."<ptr target="loc.03258_n1"/></p>

            <closer>
                <salute>Yours gratefully</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Craig McGinnis</hi></signed>
                
            </closer>

           <closer> <salute>Mr Walt Whitman,</salute><!--this appears at the bottom of the first page-->
                <salute>&#38;c. &#38;c.</salute></closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.03258.003.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
